channel.title: Lol Autorune2 news:
channel.description:
AutoRune LTD has now gone private, with the upcoming release of AutoRune 2, we cannot afford any unwanted attention; and this is how we can control it. We thank you for your support, and maybe registration oppurtunitys will be open before next christmas, but certainly not before. We are no longer accepting registrations. Please be patient, and you will see the long awaited AutoRune 2. If you already have an account at AutoRune, you may continue to the forums here: http://autoruneltd.co.uk/private/.
The link at the bottom doesnt even work. I was gonna see what was going on, or what new excuses for the "delay" was, lol.(No I did not buy an auth)

item.title: Lol Autorune2 news:
item.dc:creator: @Icewolf Icewolf
item.description:
@Icewolf wrote:

It's a HYIP, or, High-Yield-Investment-Progam. It basically asks you to invest a certain amount of money, generally about 10 to 20 dollars at minimum, or up to $10,000 maximum. Every day, you surf a certain amount of site using an automated script, at the end of which, you get credited with a certain percentage of your investment to your account, usually about 12%. At the end of a certain period of time, for example 12 days, you get the amount of money that was credited to your account, in the case of 12% interest, you would get a 144% return.

These are almost always a scam, and it's simple to see why. Where does the money come from?
